// RUN: tcrv-opt %s --split-input-file --verify-diagnostics | FileCheck %s

// The tcrv_rvv.iq2_xs_q8_k_block_dot op makes the COMPLETE ggml
// ggml_vec_dot_iq2_xs_q8_K GRID-codebook super-block dot-product STRUCTURE first-class
// in the typed RVV body -- the SECOND member of the deep IQ tail, the SIBLING of
// iq2_xxs. It REUSES iq2_xxs's grid + sign mechanism (each weight value indexes a
// packed uint64 GRID codebook, the SIGN plane ksigns_iq2xs[128]/kmask, the integer
// bsum fold, the 0.125f) with THREE structural deltas: a 512-entry grid, a 9-bit
// index read DIRECTLY from each uint16 qs word (q2[l]&511 / q2[l]>>9 -- NO aux1
// packing), and an EXPLICIT per-sub-block scales[] array carrying two 4-bit scales
// (ls1 for groups 0,1 / ls2 for groups 2,3). It consumes the iq2_xs weight base (vx),
// the q8_K activation base (vy), the fp32 output (s), the runtime element count (n),
// and the active vl token, and carries the super-block-format structural facts PLUS
// the grid (512 int64) + ksigns (128 int32) tables as typed attrs (I4 mirror). The
// verifier is fail-closed (I7) on a wrong kind / scale model / block-format fact /
// grid/ksigns size / operand C type.

// CHECK-LABEL: tcrv.exec.kernel @iq2_xs_q8_k_block_dot_accepts_ggml_abi

